  "_crew_status_note": "'assets' is not a status. It is machine-translation debris: French 'actif' (active) was translated as the English noun 'assets' (as in actifs, a balance sheet). 22 crews carry it, including the Straw Hats. This is the single best example of why the raw feed can never reach the UI. One crew (Gyro's, id 52) and one boat carry the status 'arr�t�' — 'arrêté' (halted) with two bytes already destroyed. The mojibake is stored as an ESCAPED \\ufffd in the upstream JSON, so a byte-level grep for U+FFFD across data/raw/ reports ZERO. It only appears after json.load(). That is why the U+FFFD guard runs on the parsed object, not the file bytes.",
